Well, Dandain to counter your first argument. Blacklisting<br>
already exists whether you like it or not. Consider all the guilds for example. To apply to one you have to have a reference from someone inside who can vouch for you. That's just a sample evidence that i could come up with on spur of my the moment. I have no problem sharing or giving up camp to newbies who can actually gain exp and loot as a group, because I remember what is it like growing to be one of those.<br>
Regarding faction and quests, it's just a matter of being respectful and ask simple question like whether i can please have the goblin ears or the hits on the mobs for faction. Done. Nobody is going to refuse you, especially if you help them with a bit of this or that. I'm not going to argue how everyone plays his game, yet the fact that there are play nice rules, means that there are limits to what people can do...<br>
